WEBVTT

02:58.512 --> 03:00.381
It's okay.

03:00.381 --> 03:01.715
Relax.

03:01.715 --> 03:04.318
I'm not gonna hurt you.

03:04.318 --> 03:07.187
I'm just gonna learn about you
for a little while.

03:07.187 --> 03:08.722
Is that okay?

03:14.962 --> 03:16.730
I'm gonna name you Kerolien

03:16.730 --> 03:18.532
after my friend at school.

03:18.532 --> 03:20.268
She's really nice.

03:20.268 --> 03:23.937
But she farts in class sometimes
and pretends like she didn't.

03:23.937 --> 03:25.773
So, please don't do that,

03:25.773 --> 03:27.641
'cause you're sharing
this jar now,

03:27.641 --> 03:30.711
and the others won't like you
if you smell. Okay?

04:08.416 --> 04:10.351
Hi there.

04:11.652 --> 04:12.886
I'm not from around here,

04:12.886 --> 04:15.323
but I was hoping to make
some new friends.

04:20.227 --> 04:22.963
Can I talk to you
for a little bit?

04:27.034 --> 04:30.438
I... I don't talk to strangers.

04:31.472 --> 04:32.640
Of course you don't.

04:32.640 --> 04:35.242
You shouldn't. You're smart.

04:36.644 --> 04:39.179
But I'm here to be your friend,

04:39.179 --> 04:41.949
so, hopefully, we won't
be strangers for too long.

04:41.949 --> 04:44.485
What's your name?

04:44.485 --> 04:46.554
Wenling.

04:46.554 --> 04:48.389
But everyone calls me Wen.

04:48.389 --> 04:50.424
Well, it's nice
to meet you, Wen.

04:51.425 --> 04:53.226
My name's Leonard.

05:00.000 --> 05:02.770
I see you're catching grasshoppers.

05:02.770 --> 05:04.838
Can I help you?

05:05.639 --> 05:08.308
Um, I guess so.

05:08.308 --> 05:11.445
I loved catching grasshoppers
when I was your age.

05:19.820 --> 05:22.155
- Oh, you're really good.
- Thanks, Wen.

05:22.155 --> 05:24.358
Can you pass me the jar
there, please?

05:27.294 --> 05:28.796
Wait.

05:28.796 --> 05:30.731
Let the ones inside
calm down a bit.

05:30.731 --> 05:32.933
We don't want them to panic.

05:36.069 --> 05:38.572
There you go.

05:38.572 --> 05:40.040
Are you just a natural,

05:40.040 --> 05:41.575
or did someone teach you
how to catch grasshoppers?

05:41.575 --> 05:43.711
Daddy Eric taught me.

05:43.711 --> 05:45.212
I'm studying them.

05:45.212 --> 05:48.649
I'm gonna take care of animals
when I grow up.

05:49.450 --> 05:51.318
You call your dad
by his first name?

05:52.119 --> 05:54.321
It's so they know
who I'm talking to.

05:54.321 --> 05:57.090
There's Daddy Eric
and Daddy Andrew.

05:58.225 --> 06:01.128
All the other kids at school
only have one dad.

06:01.128 --> 06:04.432
All the Disney Channel shows
only have one dad, too.

06:06.033 --> 06:07.701
Well, does that bother you?

06:07.701 --> 06:09.169
No.

06:09.169 --> 06:11.405
Except when my
guidance counselor keeps saying

06:11.405 --> 06:14.107
how it's so great
that I have two dads.

06:14.107 --> 06:15.643
For some reason,
it makes me feel like

06:15.643 --> 06:17.445
she's saying the opposite.

06:26.954 --> 06:28.321
What's wrong?

06:30.791 --> 06:32.392
Nothing.

06:32.392 --> 06:34.161
Nothing at all.

06:34.161 --> 06:35.796
How old are you, Wen?

06:35.796 --> 06:37.898
I'll be eight in six days.

06:37.898 --> 06:40.701
Well, happy almost-birthday.

06:40.701 --> 06:43.604
In fact, it just so happens

06:43.604 --> 06:45.439
that I have something for you.

06:45.439 --> 06:47.007
I saw it,
and I thought it was pretty,

06:47.007 --> 06:48.442
so I decided to keep it.

06:48.442 --> 06:51.278
So, consider it
an early birthday present.

06:52.212 --> 06:53.380
And if you don't like it,

06:53.380 --> 06:55.749
we can play a game
with it instead.

06:55.749 --> 06:57.350
What kind of game?

06:57.350 --> 07:00.320
We'll take turns pulling petals
off and asking questions,

07:00.320 --> 07:03.190
and by the time we're done,
we'll know each other better.

07:03.190 --> 07:06.126
- Be better friends.
- Hmm, 'kay.

07:06.960 --> 07:09.029
What's your favorite movie?

07:09.029 --> 07:10.631
Kiki's Delivery Service.

07:11.665 --> 07:13.634
I haven't seen that.

07:13.634 --> 07:15.603
I'll check it out.

07:15.603 --> 07:17.237
Okay, your turn.

07:20.741 --> 07:22.910
Why are you here?

07:26.580 --> 07:28.015
Leonard?

07:30.651 --> 07:32.553
Why am I here?

07:33.721 --> 07:36.590
Well, I suppose I'm here
to make friends with you

07:36.590 --> 07:38.258
and your dads.

07:38.258 --> 07:40.193
Maybe catch some more grasshoppers.

07:42.730 --> 07:45.365
How'd you get that tiny
little scar on your lip?

07:47.835 --> 07:49.537
I'm so sorry, Wen.

07:50.370 --> 07:52.405
I shouldn't have asked that.

07:52.405 --> 07:55.976
It's... It's too personal,
even for this game.

07:55.976 --> 07:57.177
It's okay.

07:57.177 --> 07:58.746
My lip was broken
when I was born.

07:58.746 --> 08:03.083
My dads said it took a lot
of doctors to fix it.

08:03.083 --> 08:04.752
Well, I don't have a scar
like you,

08:04.752 --> 08:07.287
but if you could look inside,

08:07.287 --> 08:09.590
you'd see that my heart
is broken.

08:09.590 --> 08:11.491
Why is it broken?

08:11.491 --> 08:14.294
Because of what I have
to do today.

08:14.294 --> 08:15.963
What do you have to do?

08:22.069 --> 08:24.137
Are they your friends?

08:25.105 --> 08:27.340
You're my friend, Wen.

08:27.340 --> 08:30.410
No matter what happens,
I want you to remember that.

08:30.410 --> 08:35.549
The others who are coming are
more like people I work with.

08:37.384 --> 08:41.488
You see, the four of us have
a very important job to do.

08:41.488 --> 08:44.825
In fact, it might be
the most important job

08:44.825 --> 08:47.595
in the history of the world.

08:55.669 --> 08:57.204
This isn't about you, Wen.

08:57.204 --> 08:58.606
Or your dads.

08:58.606 --> 08:59.873
Okay?

09:00.708 --> 09:03.210
You haven't done anything wrong,
but I'm afraid the three of you

09:03.210 --> 09:05.646
are gonna have to make
some tough decisions.

09:05.646 --> 09:07.147
Terrible decisions.

09:07.147 --> 09:09.783
And I wish with all my broken
heart that you didn't have to.

09:09.783 --> 09:12.052
Wen!

09:13.754 --> 09:15.956
Your dads won't want
to let us in.

09:15.956 --> 09:18.258
You have to tell them they must.

09:18.258 --> 09:20.628
Otherwise, we're gonna have
to find our own way in.

09:20.628 --> 09:22.462
Do you understand?

09:23.831 --> 09:25.833
Wen, tell me you understand!

09:35.108 --> 09:36.744
♪ Oh

09:36.744 --> 09:38.445
- ♪ Love is always better...

09:40.580 --> 09:42.482
- This isn't bad.
- The cheese is good.

09:42.482 --> 09:44.317
See? Factual proof.
There she is.

09:44.317 --> 09:45.585
You didn't need to check on her.

09:45.585 --> 09:47.154
You have to come inside
right now.

09:47.154 --> 09:48.588
There's strangers,
and they want to come in,

09:48.588 --> 09:50.157
- and they're scary!
- Whoa, whoa, slow down.

09:50.157 --> 09:52.325
- Hurry, now!
- Okay, okay, I'm coming.

09:52.325 --> 09:54.527
- We're coming inside.
- God, okay.

09:54.527 --> 09:56.563
- Come on!
- Honey, what's happening?

09:56.563 --> 09:58.231
- Tell me what's so...
- Relax, relax. Okay. It's okay.

09:58.231 --> 10:01.401
- It's okay.
- Wen, what's up?

10:01.401 --> 10:04.037
Wen, Wen, it's okay.
Listen, sweetie. What happened?

10:04.037 --> 10:05.172
What scared you?

10:05.172 --> 10:06.940
There... there were four
of them.

10:06.940 --> 10:09.142
The big one, his name's Leonard.

10:09.142 --> 10:11.478
He... he says
we have to help them.

10:11.478 --> 10:13.313
He says they have
the most important job

10:13.313 --> 10:15.816
in the history of the world.

10:17.818 --> 10:19.486
Jehovah's Witnesses?

10:19.486 --> 10:20.788
Great.

10:20.788 --> 10:23.290
They have these weapons.

10:37.604 --> 10:39.907
Hello in there.

10:39.907 --> 10:41.308
My name is Leonard,

10:41.308 --> 10:43.443
and I'm here
with some associates of mine.

10:43.443 --> 10:45.345
Can you open the door, please?

10:50.550 --> 10:53.120
This guy is frigging huge.

10:53.120 --> 10:55.088
What do we do?

10:56.223 --> 10:58.191
I don't know. Um...

10:58.191 --> 11:00.460
tell them to go away nicely?

11:01.929 --> 11:04.531
Hi. Uh, hello, Leonard. We...

11:04.531 --> 11:06.533
Is that Daddy Andrew
or Daddy Eric?

11:06.533 --> 11:08.568
I met your delightful daughter
Wen already.

11:08.568 --> 11:12.105
She's so thoughtful and kind.
You two should be very proud.

11:13.974 --> 11:15.475
This is Eric.

11:15.475 --> 11:17.677
Is there something
we can help you with?

11:17.677 --> 11:19.012
There is.

11:19.012 --> 11:20.580
Why don't you open the door?

11:20.580 --> 11:22.282
It'll be easier if we speak
face-to-face.

11:22.282 --> 11:23.784
Tell them to go away.

11:23.784 --> 11:25.585
Please make them go away.

11:25.585 --> 11:26.519
Wen, please.

11:26.519 --> 11:28.922
Uh, we weren't expecting visitors.

11:28.922 --> 11:31.859
I don't want to sound rude,
but we'd like to be left alone.

11:31.859 --> 11:33.360
I understand.

11:33.360 --> 11:35.328
And I'm sorry to intrude
on your vacation,

11:35.328 --> 11:38.165
especially in such
a beautiful place as this.

11:38.165 --> 11:39.399
Make them go away!

11:39.399 --> 11:41.001
Wen.

11:41.001 --> 11:43.370
You should know that
this isn't easy for us, either.

11:43.370 --> 11:45.839
None of us have been
to this lake before.

11:45.839 --> 11:47.741
And the four of us,
we never thought

11:47.741 --> 11:50.210
we'd be here talking
to you nice people.

11:54.381 --> 11:56.383
Who else is out there with you?

11:56.383 --> 11:58.385
I'm here with Sabrina, Adriane
and Redmond.

11:58.385 --> 11:59.887
And the four of us are here

11:59.887 --> 12:03.490
because we're trying to save
a whole bunch of people.

12:03.490 --> 12:04.958
Eric, come here. Come here.

12:04.958 --> 12:07.160
But we need
your help to do that.

12:07.160 --> 12:09.129
We can't do anything
without you,

12:09.129 --> 12:10.697
and speaking through a door

12:10.697 --> 12:14.001
is making a difficult
conversation near impossible.

12:14.001 --> 12:15.602
What?

12:19.940 --> 12:21.909
There's a woman
carrying something

12:21.909 --> 12:23.610
that looks like a pick
with a chain

12:23.610 --> 12:25.678
and a mallet head at the end.

12:29.216 --> 12:31.184
I'm calling the police now.

12:38.892 --> 12:41.361
This can't be right.
There's no dial tone.

12:41.361 --> 12:43.030
What?

12:43.030 --> 12:44.497
I checked it when we got here.

12:44.497 --> 12:45.966
Is the battery dead?

12:45.966 --> 12:47.567
The battery's not dead.
It's not dialing.

12:48.768 --> 12:52.072
Like I said, we need to talk.

12:52.072 --> 12:53.941
We don't have a choice.

12:55.608 --> 12:57.277
Yeah, well,
we don't have a choice, either!

12:57.277 --> 12:58.645
We're calling the cops!

12:58.645 --> 13:02.415
Hey, um,
we know you can't do that.

13:02.415 --> 13:04.617
None of our phones get service
out here, either.

13:04.617 --> 13:07.921
And sorry,
we had to cut the phone line.

13:14.027 --> 13:17.230
Wen. Wen.
Wen. We-Wen, give me the phone.

13:17.230 --> 13:18.665
We don't mean to rush you,

13:18.665 --> 13:21.734
but we're a little pressed
for time.

13:21.734 --> 13:24.838
Please open the door so we can
have a real conversation.

13:24.838 --> 13:26.907
If you want to talk, then why
do you... -Shh. -Wen, Wen.

13:26.907 --> 13:29.276
...have those scary weapons
with you? -Shh, shh. Wen. Wen.

13:29.276 --> 13:31.111
They're not weapons, Wen.

13:31.111 --> 13:32.779
They're tools.

13:32.779 --> 13:34.347
-
Just open the goddamn door!

13:34.347 --> 13:36.049
We're coming in either way.

13:36.049 --> 13:37.851
The hell you are! I have a gun!

13:38.986 --> 13:40.687
You brought it here?

13:40.687 --> 13:43.190
Yes and no. It's in the safe
in the back of the truck.

13:43.190 --> 13:44.757
He's lying.

13:44.757 --> 13:46.626
Show us what you're packing,
Daddy Andrew!

13:46.626 --> 13:48.061
We all like show-and-tell.

13:48.061 --> 13:49.462
You'll see it when I'm
pointing it at your head,

13:49.462 --> 13:51.031
you piece of crap!

13:51.031 --> 13:52.699
What's wrong with you?
You're not helping.

13:52.699 --> 13:54.134
- You're upsetting him.
- What?

13:54.134 --> 13:55.768
I'm sorry.

13:55.768 --> 14:00.740
Redmond is as anxious
and passionate as we all are.

14:02.809 --> 14:05.845
I'm giving you one last chance
to open the door.

14:18.258 --> 14:19.859
They're breaking in!

14:34.241 --> 14:36.543
Andrew, couch!

14:36.543 --> 14:38.011
Good job, Wen. Keep going.

14:40.380 --> 14:41.748
Push it.

14:44.217 --> 14:45.818
Okay.

14:59.132 --> 15:00.367
Daddy Andrew!

15:08.475 --> 15:10.377
I got you, baby.

15:28.495 --> 15:30.964
They're in the basement.

15:30.964 --> 15:32.966
One is in the back,
one is downstairs.

15:32.966 --> 15:35.702
Let's make a run for it
to the car.

15:35.702 --> 15:37.904
I've got the keys.

15:44.277 --> 15:46.213
It doesn't have to be like this.

15:46.213 --> 15:48.948
Get Wen out of here.

15:57.090 --> 15:59.159
Eric!

15:59.159 --> 16:00.460
Let me help him.

16:00.460 --> 16:01.828
- Wait...
- Don't touch him!

16:01.828 --> 16:03.830
I'm a nurse! He's hurt!

16:05.965 --> 16:09.002
Stop! Stop.

16:14.041 --> 16:15.875
Eric.

16:15.875 --> 16:17.544
Daddy Eric.

16:17.544 --> 16:19.446
Please get up.
We have to go, Daddy.

16:23.283 --> 16:25.285
Eric, wake up.

16:25.285 --> 16:27.554
Wake up, Eric!

16:59.119 --> 17:00.287
Shh.

17:00.287 --> 17:01.954
Shh, you'll be okay.

17:02.755 --> 17:06.326
Andrew, that's enough.

17:20.107 --> 17:21.708
♪ To illustrate

17:21.708 --> 17:23.643
♪ My last remark

17:23.643 --> 17:26.979
♪ Jonah in the whale,
Noah in the ark ♪

17:26.979 --> 17:29.749
♪ Tell me, what did they do...

17:29.749 --> 17:31.718
I like your fridge.

17:31.718 --> 17:33.953
Thanks, Mom.

17:33.953 --> 17:35.822
♪ Man, they said we got to

17:35.822 --> 17:39.559
♪ Ac-cent-tchu-ate
the positive ♪

17:39.559 --> 17:42.595
♪ And e-lim-i-nate
the negative ♪

17:42.595 --> 17:46.199
♪ And hang on
to that affirmative ♪

17:46.199 --> 17:48.835
♪ But don't mess,
don't mess with... ♪

17:57.377 --> 18:00.547
They drove for seven hours
and stayed 45 minutes.

18:00.547 --> 18:03.283
I'm sorry.

18:04.284 --> 18:06.186
What do you expect?

18:10.823 --> 18:14.194
That's my mom
asking how it's going.

18:14.194 --> 18:16.796
Well, you can tell her
you were wrong.

18:18.665 --> 18:20.200
Andrew.

18:27.440 --> 18:29.676
Always together.

18:37.984 --> 18:40.220
- Hi.

18:43.523 --> 18:44.991
Thanks, Custard.

18:44.991 --> 18:48.328
This is a very important
cupcake order.

18:49.796 --> 18:52.532
Let me see if this helps.

18:52.532 --> 18:53.800
Is that better?

18:58.338 --> 19:01.241
Try not to move.

19:01.241 --> 19:02.675
Almost done.

19:02.675 --> 19:04.076
I have to finish

19:04.076 --> 19:06.279
this special order
before tomorrow.

19:06.279 --> 19:09.282
It needs to be purr-fect.

19:10.850 --> 19:13.085
Can you turn that down?

19:13.853 --> 19:15.355
We did when you asked before,

19:15.355 --> 19:17.524
but I'll do it again.

19:22.329 --> 19:23.763
Is Eric cleaned up?

19:23.763 --> 19:27.300
He's cleaned up, yeah,
but severely concussed.

19:31.170 --> 19:32.639
Hey, Eric.

19:33.440 --> 19:35.875
You feeling any better?

19:35.875 --> 19:39.178
I'm... I'm so sorry.

19:41.514 --> 19:44.584
I've never watched this show
before, but-but I like it.

19:44.584 --> 19:47.320
The characters, um,
they seem curious and good.

19:47.320 --> 19:51.090
I get the sense that it
explores or teaches empathy

19:51.090 --> 19:53.693
and tolerance,
and that's just lovely.

19:53.693 --> 19:57.196
Empathy and tolerance?

19:57.196 --> 19:58.898
Is that what you're here
to talk about

19:58.898 --> 20:00.900
now that you have the queers
tied up?

20:00.900 --> 20:02.835
Oh.

20:02.835 --> 20:04.971
Andrew, I assure you
that we're not here

20:04.971 --> 20:07.507
with hate or prejudice
in our hearts. Not at all.

20:07.507 --> 20:10.477
We don't have one
homophobic bone in our bodies.

20:10.477 --> 20:12.245
I don't hate anybody.

20:12.245 --> 20:14.914
I do have conflicted feelings
about this door.

20:16.115 --> 20:18.184
You have to believe that.

20:18.184 --> 20:20.620
But we had no idea
you were a single-sex couple

20:20.620 --> 20:23.390
until we got here.

20:23.390 --> 20:25.292
That one was a surprise.

20:25.292 --> 20:29.028
Well, I guess if you promise,
then I have to believe you.

20:29.829 --> 20:32.265
I mean, we're normal people
just like you.

20:32.265 --> 20:35.335
- We have no choice.
- There's always a choice!

20:36.202 --> 20:38.871
He's right about that.

20:38.871 --> 20:42.375
Our choices make our destiny.

20:42.375 --> 20:45.244
I almost got that tattooed.

20:48.815 --> 20:51.017
Okay, you're right, Andrew.

20:51.017 --> 20:52.652
There's always a choice.

20:52.652 --> 20:55.388
So we choose to be here.

20:55.388 --> 20:58.325
Can everyone come in here, please?

20:58.325 --> 21:00.460
It's almost time.

21:00.460 --> 21:02.395
Time for what?

21:02.395 --> 21:04.497
You don't need us tied up.

21:05.465 --> 21:08.234
You said you were here to talk,
so we'll talk.

21:18.911 --> 21:22.281
Hi, Eric, Wen...

21:23.483 --> 21:26.085
...and Andrew.

21:26.085 --> 21:28.254
My name is Sabrina.

21:28.254 --> 21:31.991
I live in Southern California.

21:31.991 --> 21:34.727
I live in a town
you've probably never heard of.

21:34.727 --> 21:41.000
I have been a post-op nurse
for almost five years.

21:41.000 --> 21:45.237
I used most of my savings

21:45.237 --> 21:47.306
to come out to Pennsylvania,

21:47.306 --> 21:50.877
to come here to talk
with you guys.

21:56.015 --> 21:59.352
I have a little
half sister back home...

22:00.152 --> 22:04.123
...and, Wen,
you kind of remind me of her.

22:14.033 --> 22:15.702
Well, I think you-you guys
already know

22:15.702 --> 22:17.504
my name is Leonard.

22:17.504 --> 22:19.639
And, uh,

22:19.639 --> 22:21.841
I'm good at catching
grasshoppers, right, Wen?

22:27.079 --> 22:28.581
I'm from Chicago.

22:28.581 --> 22:29.849
I'm a second grade teacher,

22:29.849 --> 22:33.520
and I run
the after-school program.

22:33.520 --> 22:35.522
I'm also a bartender. I...

22:35.522 --> 22:37.557
Okay. Me?

22:37.557 --> 22:38.858
Am I next?

22:38.858 --> 22:40.427
Hi there.

22:40.427 --> 22:43.162
I'm Redmond, and I like
long walks on the beach,

22:43.162 --> 22:44.797
- and I like beer.
- Hey.

22:44.797 --> 22:46.198
We already discussed this.

22:46.198 --> 22:48.234
They deserve to know who we are.

22:48.234 --> 22:53.305
We wasted time for this guy
to wake up.

22:53.305 --> 22:56.643
You know, this get-to-know-you
stuff doesn't matter at all.

22:56.643 --> 23:00.647
Doesn't change what we have
to do or what they have to do.

23:00.647 --> 23:05.217
When you say stuff like that,
you sound how you sound,

23:05.217 --> 23:08.020
okay, you just scare them,
you make it less likely

23:08.020 --> 23:10.923
that they'll believe us
or cooperate.

23:10.923 --> 23:14.427
Okay, okay, my turn it is.

23:14.427 --> 23:17.196
I live in Medford, Massachusetts.

23:17.196 --> 23:19.131
I work for the gas company,

23:19.131 --> 23:22.969
making sure houses
and apartments don't blow up.

23:22.969 --> 23:25.938
I'm single,
if you can believe that.

23:27.507 --> 23:31.377
I've done some time,
as they say.

23:32.945 --> 23:36.015
Did a lot of, uh...

23:36.015 --> 23:40.453
questionable stuff
when I was young and stupid.

23:41.821 --> 23:44.356
But I'm much better now.

23:48.761 --> 23:50.763
And my father used to beat
the shit out of me,

23:50.763 --> 23:52.098
like Andrew just did.

23:53.800 --> 23:56.736
Wish I could go back in time,

23:56.736 --> 23:58.938
give the kid-me this thing.

23:58.938 --> 24:01.708
May I speak now?

24:01.708 --> 24:03.342
I hope I don't sound confusing.

24:03.342 --> 24:05.444
Hold on, hold on a second.

24:05.444 --> 24:07.179
Wh...

24:07.179 --> 24:09.549
We get that you guys
are a part of some group

24:09.549 --> 24:13.720
and it sounds like,
it sounds like you want to...

24:13.720 --> 24:15.522
fix things.

24:15.522 --> 24:17.156
To help.

24:17.156 --> 24:18.658
Eric, you don't have
to try to talk...

24:18.658 --> 24:20.459
I... No, no, I'm okay.
I want to say this.

24:20.459 --> 24:24.664
If you're try...
trying to recruit us,

24:24.664 --> 24:26.533
I mean, why else bother

24:26.533 --> 24:29.702
introducing yourselves to us, right?

24:29.702 --> 24:36.042
If you're trying to change us
or make us different,

24:36.042 --> 24:38.878
all of this...

24:38.878 --> 24:41.280
this isn't the way.

24:43.149 --> 24:45.284
Can someone put the curtain
on the back door?

24:45.284 --> 24:46.853
What's wrong with Eric?

24:46.853 --> 24:48.154
When you have a concussion,

24:48.154 --> 24:49.689
you're extremely sensitive
to light.

24:49.689 --> 24:51.323
Well, there-there's nothing
we can do about that now.

24:51.323 --> 24:52.825
Well, he's only gonna
get better if he rests

24:52.825 --> 24:54.594
in a darkened room
or if we make it dark in here.

24:54.594 --> 24:56.295
We shouldn't move him
until we make our proposal.

24:56.295 --> 24:57.730
He might need to be
in a darkened room for days,

24:57.730 --> 24:59.799
- not just a few hours.
- You're not separating me

24:59.799 --> 25:01.167
from Andrew and Wen.

25:01.167 --> 25:03.570
I'll see what I can do
with the curtains.

25:03.570 --> 25:04.904
So, whatever.

25:04.904 --> 25:07.874
I'm, um, I'm Adriane.

25:07.874 --> 25:10.643
Yeah, I-I've been a lot
of things, but-but right now,

25:10.643 --> 25:14.647
or, um, before I got up here,
I-I was a line cook

25:14.647 --> 25:19.185
at a Mexican restaurant
in-in Dupont Circle, D.C.

25:19.986 --> 25:22.021
I love to feed people.

25:22.021 --> 25:24.824
It feels like it's more
than food to me.

25:24.824 --> 25:27.459
Um, God, what else?

25:27.459 --> 25:28.928
Uh...

25:28.928 --> 25:31.964
Oh, I have, um, I have two cats.

25:31.964 --> 25:33.499
And you'd love them, Wen.

25:33.499 --> 25:37.069
Their names are Riff and Raff.

25:37.069 --> 25:39.138
Do you like cats, Wen?

25:39.138 --> 25:41.708
You don't have to answer her, sweetie.

25:41.708 --> 25:43.409
Sorry, Wen.

25:43.409 --> 25:45.277
Maybe I'll put it back on
later, okay?

25:45.277 --> 25:47.980
Forget the curtains.

25:47.980 --> 25:50.016
It's time.

26:05.031 --> 26:08.901
The four of us are here
to prevent the apocalypse.

26:10.069 --> 26:13.305
We-- and when I say "we,"
I mean everyone in this cabin--

26:13.305 --> 26:17.143
can stop it from happening,
but only with your help.

26:19.445 --> 26:23.382
Ultimately,
whether the world ends or not

26:23.382 --> 26:26.719
is completely up to you three.

26:27.854 --> 26:31.423
You are having a psychological
break of some kind.

26:40.499 --> 26:43.703
Your family must choose
to willingly sacrifice

26:43.703 --> 26:45.071
one of the three of you

26:45.071 --> 26:47.674
in order to prevent
the apocalypse.

26:50.777 --> 26:54.714
After you make what I know
is an impossible decision,

26:54.714 --> 26:57.549
you must then kill
the one you choose.

27:00.820 --> 27:03.289
If you fail to choose,

27:03.289 --> 27:07.660
or if you fail to follow through
with the sacrifice,

27:07.660 --> 27:10.096
the world will end.

27:10.096 --> 27:13.465
You three will live,

27:13.465 --> 27:16.168
but the rest of humanity,

27:16.168 --> 27:21.040
seven billion plus...

27:21.040 --> 27:22.541
will perish.

27:25.978 --> 27:27.546
They're lunatics.

27:28.614 --> 27:30.449
And you will all live
long enough

27:30.449 --> 27:34.687
to witness the horror
of the end of everything.

27:34.687 --> 27:39.826
And you will be left to wander
the devastated planet alone.

27:41.427 --> 27:46.265
Permanently
and cosmically... alone.

27:47.734 --> 27:50.436
Leonard.

27:51.270 --> 27:53.539
We haven't done anything wrong.

27:53.539 --> 27:55.274
I agree with you. You haven't.

27:55.274 --> 27:59.611
You haven't done anything wrong
to... to deserve this burden.

28:03.115 --> 28:07.386
You're just the family chosen
to decide for us in this time.

28:17.563 --> 28:19.832
Look,
we're not here to hurt you.

28:19.832 --> 28:22.334
If we wanted to hurt you,
we would've used duct tape

28:22.334 --> 28:24.871
- instead of ropes.
- You stop.

28:27.206 --> 28:28.875
You have to understand
that we cannot

28:28.875 --> 28:31.944
and will not choose who has
to be sacrificed for you.

28:31.944 --> 28:35.681
And just as importantly,
we cannot act for you.

28:35.681 --> 28:37.716
And you cannot kill yourselves.

28:38.650 --> 28:40.619
We're not choosing anyone.

28:40.619 --> 28:42.721
We're not sacrificing anyone.

28:42.721 --> 28:44.590
Not now, not ever.

28:44.590 --> 28:47.559
Even if it means the death
of everyone else in the world?

28:47.559 --> 28:49.728
Yes. Even if I believe
the world was at stake,

28:49.728 --> 28:53.099
which I don't,
that's what it means.

28:53.099 --> 28:54.767
I would watch the world die
a hundred times over

28:54.767 --> 28:57.203
- before having to...
- Christ.

28:57.203 --> 28:59.205
Waste of time.

28:59.205 --> 29:02.408
They're never gonna choose
to do this.

29:02.408 --> 29:04.410
And I don't blame them.

29:04.410 --> 29:06.578
- Who would ever choose...
- Shut up, Redmond.

29:06.578 --> 29:09.348
You just vomit
everything you think.

29:09.348 --> 29:11.851
Oh, God, we are so screwed.

29:11.851 --> 29:13.685
Okay,

29:13.685 --> 29:16.488
you need to listen
to this part, too.

29:16.488 --> 29:18.224
I've been shown exactly
what will happen

29:18.224 --> 29:20.326
if you choose not to make
a sacrifice.

29:20.326 --> 29:22.594
We've all been shown.

29:22.594 --> 29:25.798
We couldn't stop drawing
the visions we saw.

29:25.798 --> 29:30.002
I actually thought
something was wrong with me,

29:30.002 --> 29:31.938
but the visions were so strong,

29:31.938 --> 29:35.808
so specific and so, so real.

29:35.808 --> 29:38.477
Sabrina, Adriane and Redmond,
they had the visions, too.

29:38.477 --> 29:43.315
So, that led us
to each other and...

29:43.315 --> 29:46.685
and that led us here
to this exact cabin.

29:46.685 --> 29:50.222
We have no idea
why we were picked.

29:59.465 --> 30:01.633
First, the cities will drown.

30:01.633 --> 30:06.238
The oceans will swell
and rise up into a great fist

30:06.238 --> 30:09.275
and pound all the buildings
and people into the sand,

30:09.275 --> 30:10.776
and drag everything out to sea.

30:10.776 --> 30:12.644
There is something
wrong with you,

30:12.644 --> 30:15.781
with all of you,
if you believe this.

30:15.781 --> 30:18.417
Then a terrible plague
will descend

30:18.417 --> 30:19.751
and people will writhe
with fever,

30:19.751 --> 30:21.520
and mucus will fill their lungs.

30:21.520 --> 30:22.922
This is psychotic.

30:22.922 --> 30:24.924
It's delusional.

30:24.924 --> 30:26.292
Did you try to get help?

30:26.292 --> 30:28.360
Let us go
and we'll get you help.

30:28.360 --> 30:30.029
The skies will fall
and crash to the earth

30:30.029 --> 30:31.663
like pieces of glass.

30:31.663 --> 30:34.133
And God's fingers
will scorch the earth

30:34.133 --> 30:36.668
and an everlasting darkness
will descend over humanity.

30:36.668 --> 30:39.005
You need help!

30:42.909 --> 30:45.077
This is going to happen.

30:46.412 --> 30:49.781
And we've been shown that only
your sacrifice can stop it.

30:49.781 --> 30:51.050
Shown by who?

30:51.050 --> 30:52.384
By what?

30:52.384 --> 30:53.920
Are you gonna answer that?

30:53.920 --> 30:55.554
You sound like every
fake doomsdayer

30:55.554 --> 30:58.490
on every corner of every city.

31:02.661 --> 31:06.933
Come on, talk to us.

31:06.933 --> 31:11.570
Dreams can have
many different meanings.

31:12.438 --> 31:15.841
Our part in your visions
is kind of vague.

31:15.841 --> 31:19.245
Almost like you didn't know
who would be here.

31:19.245 --> 31:21.680
Like it was random.

31:22.982 --> 31:24.583
It doesn't make sense.

31:25.417 --> 31:28.487
For every "no" you give us,

31:28.487 --> 31:32.624
we will unleash a plague
for the sins of humanity.

31:36.195 --> 31:38.497
Will you make a choice?

32:07.126 --> 32:10.296
Wait, stop.

32:10.296 --> 32:12.264
You don't need to do this.

32:12.264 --> 32:13.465
You don't need those things.

32:13.465 --> 32:15.467
You said you couldn't hurt us.

32:17.236 --> 32:19.205
What are you doing?

32:25.377 --> 32:26.912
What are you doing?
Don't touch her.

32:26.912 --> 32:30.249
Don't touch her!
Get off her, get off her!

32:30.249 --> 32:32.684
Get off of her!

32:34.453 --> 32:37.323
Wen, Wen.

32:37.323 --> 32:39.225
Run, Wen. Wen.

32:39.225 --> 32:40.559
I can't.

32:40.559 --> 32:42.728
Run.

32:50.169 --> 32:53.839
Please, God, just let us go.

33:07.919 --> 33:10.022
Fuck.

33:10.022 --> 33:11.823
I'm scared.

33:13.759 --> 33:16.128
Keep looking at me, okay?

33:17.829 --> 33:21.100
Don't you fucking look away
from me.

33:59.905 --> 34:03.909
A part of humanity
has been judged.

34:08.447 --> 34:10.149
Whatever it is you're
convinced of, it isn't real.

34:10.149 --> 34:11.817
- You don't have to do this.
- This isn't real.

34:11.817 --> 34:13.719
- It's not gonna... No!

34:57.963 --> 35:00.866
You can pray if you want.
I won't make comment.

35:09.941 --> 35:11.877
Mr. and Mrs. Brooks?

35:11.877 --> 35:14.213
Yes. My wife couldn't
be here today.

35:14.213 --> 35:16.014
This is her brother.

35:42.073 --> 35:44.610
Now tell me
this isn't a miracle.

35:48.547 --> 35:51.016
Hi. Hi, Daddy.

35:51.016 --> 35:52.684
Hi, Wen.

35:52.684 --> 35:54.886
- Hey.

35:54.886 --> 35:56.455
- Oh.
-  Oh.

36:23.949 --> 36:25.284
Adriane,

36:25.284 --> 36:27.553
can you help me out here?

36:27.553 --> 36:30.055
- Adriane.
- Hey, yeah.

36:30.055 --> 36:31.089
What?

36:31.089 --> 36:33.659
Help me take Redmond outside.

36:35.126 --> 36:37.329
We'll cover him with a blanket.

37:31.517 --> 37:33.719
Wen, I'm sorry, but I'm gonna
have to change the channel

37:33.719 --> 37:34.886
for a little bit, okay?

37:34.886 --> 37:36.355
Go fuck yourself, Mister Rogers.

37:36.355 --> 37:38.924
I want you
to try a piece of this.

37:38.924 --> 37:40.992
I want to see whether
the air fryer oven

37:40.992 --> 37:43.995
- makes it just as crispy...
- Please watch the TV.

37:43.995 --> 37:45.597
- It should be on soon.
- I'm not even gonna kid you,

37:45.597 --> 37:47.399
I really just want this.

37:47.399 --> 37:50.201
-Do you hear
that gorgeous crispy crunch?

37:50.201 --> 37:52.103
-Doesn't get
much better than that.

37:52.103 --> 37:53.705
Mmm.

37:53.705 --> 37:55.206
And it tastes amazing.

37:55.206 --> 37:57.943
Amazing fried chicken
and a lot less guilt.

38:01.913 --> 38:03.815
We continue with our coverage
of the earthquake

38:03.815 --> 38:05.951
centered in
the Aleutian Islands,

38:05.951 --> 38:07.919
which struck more than
four hours ago.

38:07.919 --> 38:10.021
The U.S. National Tsunami
Warning Center

38:10.021 --> 38:13.124
has issued a cautionary advisory
to British Columbia,

38:13.124 --> 38:15.794
Canada, and more than
a thousand miles of coast

38:15.794 --> 38:17.829
along the
American Pacific Northwest,

38:17.829 --> 38:20.732
including the cities
of Seattle and Portland.

38:20.732 --> 38:22.267
The Pacific Tsunami
Warning Center

38:22.267 --> 38:25.404
issued its strongest warning
to the islands of Hawaii.

38:25.404 --> 38:27.305
Is this what we're supposed
to see?

38:27.305 --> 38:28.940
...high schools, malls
and colleges, campuses...

38:28.940 --> 38:30.476
I explained to you
what would happen

38:30.476 --> 38:31.877
as a result of you not choosing.

38:31.877 --> 38:33.645
A plague will be released
by Redmond's death.

38:33.645 --> 38:35.080
You have to listen to me.

38:35.080 --> 38:36.348
I remember,
but this doesn't mean anything.

38:36.348 --> 38:37.516
- It doesn't mean...
- No!

38:37.516 --> 38:39.317
Just watch!

38:41.387 --> 38:43.755
I know I shouldn't yell.

38:43.755 --> 38:45.457
I know you're afraid of me,
of us.

38:45.457 --> 38:47.359
Just... please watch.

38:47.359 --> 38:48.960
...points to a sizable wave

38:48.960 --> 38:50.562
of 15 to 20 feet in height

38:50.562 --> 38:52.864
headed south towards
the Hawaiian Islands.

38:52.864 --> 38:56.568
We do have information that
the tsunami has made landfall.

38:56.568 --> 38:58.670
Now, as you can tell
from our live feed,

38:58.670 --> 39:02.140
this resort on Kauai
has already been evacuated.

39:09.280 --> 39:11.182
Our early warning
detection systems

39:11.182 --> 39:13.552
gave plenty of time
to evacuate the coasts

39:13.552 --> 39:16.254
and low-laying areas at
the affected Hawaiian Islands.

39:16.254 --> 39:17.923
No injuries or fatalities
have been reported.

39:17.923 --> 39:19.791
Please let Eric
and Wen go at least.

39:19.791 --> 39:22.093
Eric has a concussion.

39:24.295 --> 39:26.197
I'll stay.

39:26.197 --> 39:28.700
And we can talk about doomsday,
or the apocalypse,

39:28.700 --> 39:31.002
or mass traumatic events of
the 21st century all you want.

39:31.002 --> 39:32.771
I don't understand,
this isn't the...

39:32.771 --> 39:35.974
Sabrina, just keep watching.

39:35.974 --> 39:38.343
Until we see what was shown
to us.

39:44.416 --> 39:46.284
A second massive earthquake

39:46.284 --> 39:48.019
has struck in the Pacific,

39:48.019 --> 39:49.721
registering 8.6
on the Richter scale.

39:49.721 --> 39:53.291
The epicenter is only 70 miles
off the coast of Oregon

39:53.291 --> 39:56.227
in what's called
the Cascadia Subduction Zone.

39:56.227 --> 39:58.129
That's an area scientists
have long feared

39:58.129 --> 40:01.533
would produce
a catastrophic earthquake.

40:02.534 --> 40:03.969
Unbelievable.

40:03.969 --> 40:05.971
There it is.

40:05.971 --> 40:08.106
We did this.

40:08.106 --> 40:10.942
It's really fucking happening.

40:11.843 --> 40:15.146
Oh, Jesus, God.

40:15.146 --> 40:17.082
...and given the proximity
of the epicenter,

40:17.082 --> 40:20.018
people on the coast
are gonna have mere minutes

40:20.018 --> 40:21.453
to try to find shelter.

40:21.453 --> 40:24.656
A tsunami triggered by a quake
of this magnitude

40:24.656 --> 40:28.794
and proximity to the shoreline
will be massive.

40:28.794 --> 40:30.629
I-I mean, 50-foot-high bluffs

40:30.629 --> 40:33.198
along the coast
are not gonna be safe.

40:33.198 --> 40:34.666
And we've just gotten word.

40:34.666 --> 40:37.168
The tsunami has indeed hit
the Oregon shoreline

40:37.168 --> 40:41.239
and we have footage shot
minutes ago from Cannon Beach.

40:43.475 --> 40:45.677
Holy crap, this is what I saw.

40:45.677 --> 40:48.847
The same jutting rocks.

40:48.847 --> 40:50.816
Me, too.

41:32.524 --> 41:34.159
Wen,

41:34.159 --> 41:36.795
go to your room
till I tell you to come out.

41:52.043 --> 41:54.680
She didn't need to see this.

41:54.680 --> 41:57.583
Tomorrow morning,
you can make the difficult,

41:57.583 --> 42:01.219
selfless choice of sacrifice
and save the world...

42:02.353 --> 42:04.723
...or you can choose once again

42:04.723 --> 42:06.692
to let the clock move
another minute closer

42:06.692 --> 42:09.127
to permanent midnight.

42:12.163 --> 42:14.399
For the rest of today
and tonight,

42:14.399 --> 42:17.636
we'll tend to your needs
within reason.

42:17.636 --> 42:19.871
But otherwise,

42:19.871 --> 42:22.608
we'll leave you be to reflect...

42:22.608 --> 42:24.910
and talk it over.

42:24.910 --> 42:26.411
We told you.

42:26.411 --> 42:27.913
You have to believe us.

42:27.913 --> 42:29.948
It doesn't matter if we believe
your craziness.

42:29.948 --> 42:32.483
The answer is still the same.

42:32.483 --> 42:35.253
Everyone in the world can die,
as far as we're concerned.

42:35.253 --> 42:37.322
Am I right, Eric?

42:39.958 --> 42:41.526
Eric?

42:42.894 --> 42:45.063
You okay?

42:45.063 --> 42:47.599
I'm okay.

42:50.168 --> 42:52.671
I just need a moment.

42:55.340 --> 42:56.742
I have a little surprise

42:56.742 --> 42:58.376
- queued up for you.
- Ooh. Oh, a surprise.

42:58.376 --> 42:59.945
- Ooh, what's that gonna be?
- Are you ready?

43:01.613 --> 43:04.349
- Oh! -Oh!
- Yeah!

43:04.349 --> 43:05.984
- Are we gonna sing along?
- Yes, of course.

43:05.984 --> 43:08.286
- I think, I think we are.
- I don't know, I don't know.

43:08.286 --> 43:10.355
♪ Girl, to be with you

43:10.355 --> 43:12.423
♪ Is my favorite thing

43:12.423 --> 43:14.760
- ♪ Bah, dum

43:14.760 --> 43:16.194
♪ Bah, dum

43:16.194 --> 43:21.499
♪ I can't wait
till I see you again ♪

43:22.968 --> 43:24.169
Here we go. Ready?

43:24.169 --> 43:26.237
♪ I want to put on

43:26.237 --> 43:28.539
♪ My, my, my, my,
my boogie shoes ♪

43:28.539 --> 43:30.776
- Hey.
- ♪ Just to boogie with you

43:30.776 --> 43:32.143
- Hey.
- ♪ Yeah

43:32.143 --> 43:34.079
♪ I want to put on

43:34.079 --> 43:37.148
♪ My, my, my, my,
my boogie shoes ♪

43:37.148 --> 43:38.416
♪ Just to boogie with you

43:38.416 --> 43:40.251
Hey.

43:40.251 --> 43:45.090
♪ I want do it
till the sun comes up... ♪

43:53.531 --> 43:56.267
- It's gorgeous.

43:57.936 --> 43:59.771
Except for the... the main road
being further away

43:59.771 --> 44:02.774
than we thought,
I'm officially impressed.

44:02.774 --> 44:04.575
Okay.

44:04.575 --> 44:07.145
- Hey, Wen, come get your bag.
- Wen?

44:07.145 --> 44:09.180
Wen, come on.

44:09.180 --> 44:11.182
Wen, come check out the view.

44:11.182 --> 44:13.451
It's better than the website.

44:15.520 --> 44:17.823
How many grasshoppers
did you catch?

44:17.823 --> 44:19.725
Just one so far.

44:19.725 --> 44:20.926
Her name's Liv.

44:20.926 --> 44:22.227
Oh. You see any bears yet?

44:22.227 --> 44:24.029
Andrew, don't start.

44:24.029 --> 44:25.831
If we joke about it,
she won't take it seriously.

44:25.831 --> 44:28.633
We won't leave the garbage out,
we'll be fine.

44:28.633 --> 44:33.204
Wen, show Daddy Eric
your scary bear face.

44:36.541 --> 44:38.409
- Wen, run from... Run.

44:38.409 --> 44:39.778
Hey, Wenling, sweetie,
not too close.

44:39.778 --> 44:41.312
That dock might have
rusty nails.

44:41.312 --> 44:42.513
Eric, come on
with your rusty nails.

44:42.513 --> 44:44.249
We got so lucky with this place.

44:44.249 --> 44:45.683
Whoo!

44:45.683 --> 44:47.485
- Get in!

44:47.485 --> 44:49.620
- Come on, Wen!

44:50.421 --> 44:52.423
- Come on!
- Oh.

44:52.423 --> 44:54.659
- Whoo!

44:54.659 --> 44:56.661
Whoa!

44:57.729 --> 44:59.865
- Here I come!
- Eric, come!

44:59.865 --> 45:01.166
He's coming in!

45:01.166 --> 45:02.367
Oh, come on.

45:02.367 --> 45:05.070
Hold on, one second, one second.

45:05.070 --> 45:06.772
- Woo-hoo!
- Coming right at you.

45:06.772 --> 45:08.473
- Here I come.
- Yes, yes, yes!

45:13.078 --> 45:15.113
Oh. Oh, it's a cold spot.

45:15.113 --> 45:17.215
Look at you swimming.

45:20.351 --> 45:22.353
Just applying a little pressure.

45:24.355 --> 45:26.524
Told you I'm a nurse.

45:26.524 --> 45:27.926
You may not be on board

45:27.926 --> 45:29.928
with all the
"end of the world" stuff yet,

45:29.928 --> 45:32.497
but at least trust me on that.

45:32.497 --> 45:34.732
None of us wanted it
to go this way.

45:34.732 --> 45:37.502
We need you
in a clear state of mind.

45:37.502 --> 45:40.538
You've got a big decision
to make.

45:42.573 --> 45:46.477
You think I'm some kind
of religious freak, right?

45:47.445 --> 45:49.815
I would, too.

45:49.815 --> 45:51.616
Truth is,
I haven't even been to church

45:51.616 --> 45:55.053
since my grandma forced me to go
when I was little.

45:55.053 --> 45:58.156
I always thought religious stuff
was so tired and boring

45:58.156 --> 46:02.493
from another time, and people
were scared of shadows.

46:06.231 --> 46:08.766
Then the visions started.

46:12.737 --> 46:15.573
I didn't believe it at first, either.

46:17.208 --> 46:19.577
But you will.

46:24.349 --> 46:27.652
When I was a kid,
my dad used to say to me,

46:27.652 --> 46:31.422
"Trust in something
more than you."

46:33.091 --> 46:38.396
It's sort of become my mantra
these past few days.

46:39.197 --> 46:41.699
I said it
when I saw the visions.

46:41.699 --> 46:43.869
I said it when I built my weapon

46:43.869 --> 46:45.971
exactly the way
it was shown to me.

46:45.971 --> 46:47.605
I said it over and over

46:47.605 --> 46:51.409
as I passed every freeway exit
on my way here.

46:53.211 --> 46:55.646
I said it when I walked out
onto the boardwalk

46:55.646 --> 46:57.949
and I saw the others.

46:58.749 --> 47:02.520
We were all wearing the same
colors we saw in our visions.

47:02.520 --> 47:05.523
That's when I knew
I wasn't alone.

47:07.658 --> 47:09.995
And all of this...

47:12.463 --> 47:14.765
...is real.

47:16.935 --> 47:19.670
And I'm saying it
to you now, Eric,

47:19.670 --> 47:21.439
you need to trust something
more than you.

47:21.439 --> 47:25.977
You may not want to believe it,
but we're all on the same side.

47:28.246 --> 47:30.882
I'm on my family's side.

48:06.617 --> 48:09.220
Eric?

48:09.220 --> 48:11.389
You really okay?

48:12.457 --> 48:15.693
My head's still ringing,
but my vision is clearer.

48:24.802 --> 48:26.304
You know that first
earthquake happened

48:26.304 --> 48:28.139
a whole four hours ago, right?

48:28.139 --> 48:29.975
Before they showed up here.

48:29.975 --> 48:32.243
Leonard's checked his watch
a thousand times.

48:32.243 --> 48:34.612
They've been timing all of this.

48:35.413 --> 48:36.381
I know.

48:42.420 --> 48:44.489
I just don't want you to...

48:46.724 --> 48:48.559
I don't want you to be spooked
or anything.

48:48.559 --> 48:50.261
You think I believe them?

48:50.261 --> 48:51.696
No.

48:53.564 --> 48:56.334
No, it's just...

48:56.334 --> 48:57.735
With your head and all,

48:57.735 --> 48:59.337
I want to make sure
you're thinking straight.

48:59.337 --> 49:01.606
Without them trying
to manipulate us.

49:01.606 --> 49:05.076
They take you alone in there
and try and talk to you.

49:05.076 --> 49:07.678
I don't believe them.

49:12.417 --> 49:14.452
I'm trying to keep it together.

49:14.452 --> 49:15.686
This isn't gonna work.

49:15.686 --> 49:17.322
They're never gonna
believe us, man.

49:17.322 --> 49:19.290
We have to believe
in what we're doing,

49:19.290 --> 49:20.791
what our goal is here.

49:20.791 --> 49:23.661
Did you see
Redmond's fucking face?

49:23.661 --> 49:25.330
It was just crazy.

49:25.330 --> 49:27.565
Say whatever it is
you have to say to them.

49:27.565 --> 49:29.300
Convince them.

49:53.858 --> 49:56.461
- Wen!

50:00.298 --> 50:01.966
Wen!

50:07.438 --> 50:09.474
Wen!

50:14.145 --> 50:16.114
Wen!

50:41.106 --> 50:42.540
Whoa!

50:52.950 --> 50:56.121
I'm afraid the rule is
that no one's allowed to leave.

50:57.488 --> 50:58.989
Were you trying to escape, Wen?

50:58.989 --> 51:01.292
Leave her alone.

51:01.292 --> 51:03.561
I told her to do it.

51:03.561 --> 51:06.431
You're just scared, Wen.

51:06.431 --> 51:07.965
We all are.

51:07.965 --> 51:11.035
You'll ask us to choose again.

51:11.035 --> 51:13.204
Don't listen to them, Wen.

51:15.039 --> 51:17.508
We were targeted.

51:18.643 --> 51:21.078
We've always
been targeted. We...

51:21.078 --> 51:22.580
- Andrew!

51:27.885 --> 51:30.521
I knew I recognized him.

51:37.462 --> 51:39.564
Redmond...

51:39.564 --> 51:41.199
is the guy from the bar.

51:41.199 --> 51:43.234
What?

51:43.234 --> 51:44.469
Are you sure?

51:44.469 --> 51:46.737
What guy from the bar?

51:46.737 --> 51:49.740
Andrew was attacked by a man in
a bar in Boston many years ago.

51:49.740 --> 51:51.842
The man went to jail
for a short while.

51:51.842 --> 51:53.344
But his name was O'Bannon.

51:53.344 --> 51:54.779
It's him.

51:54.779 --> 51:56.181
He's gained weight
and his beard's different,

51:56.181 --> 51:57.648
but it's him.

51:58.416 --> 51:59.950
His name was Redmond.

51:59.950 --> 52:02.520
We don't know dick about him, Leonard.

52:02.520 --> 52:05.122
We all met him for the
first time on that boardwalk.

52:05.122 --> 52:06.724
Stop the bullshit!

52:06.724 --> 52:07.958
This is all some kind
of sick scam

52:07.958 --> 52:09.360
to get us to hurt each other.

52:09.360 --> 52:10.828
That's not true.

52:10.828 --> 52:12.230
We don't know
why each of us is here.

52:12.230 --> 52:13.998
It's a coincidence
the man who attacked me

52:13.998 --> 52:16.301
and had me in years of therapy
is one of your group?

52:16.301 --> 52:17.768
Go get his wallet.

52:17.768 --> 52:20.638
I'll show you his name
isn't Redmond.

52:21.439 --> 52:22.607
No, we're not doing that.

52:22.607 --> 52:24.642
Why?!

52:25.743 --> 52:28.446
Because it doesn't matter
what his name is.

52:28.446 --> 52:30.448
Okay? We all had the visions.

52:30.448 --> 52:31.849
This has to be exact.

52:31.849 --> 52:34.619
Everything has to be right.

52:34.619 --> 52:36.086
Didn't he tell us
about this cabin

52:36.086 --> 52:37.722
on the message board first?

52:37.722 --> 52:39.023
And then we all had visions
of the cabin?

52:39.023 --> 52:40.425
I don't know. It...

52:40.425 --> 52:42.493
No, we had the visions first.

52:42.493 --> 52:44.128
Message board?

52:47.765 --> 52:50.034
Look, we're not doubting
why we're here.

52:53.504 --> 52:55.540
Go to sleep.

52:55.540 --> 52:57.208
The sun will rise,

52:57.208 --> 52:59.910
maybe for the last time
for all of us.

52:59.910 --> 53:02.380
The premise of your scam
is flawed.

53:03.281 --> 53:05.850
I'm a human rights attorney, Leonard.

53:05.850 --> 53:07.418
How about I show you
photos of kids

53:07.418 --> 53:11.021
who have been tortured
and killed, lying in piles?

53:11.021 --> 53:12.823
You want to make a case
for humanity to go on,

53:12.823 --> 53:14.625
you're gonna lose.

53:23.301 --> 53:27.104
This is a picture of some
of the kids I coach.

53:27.104 --> 53:30.541
This year, the boys had
a record of three and eight.

53:30.541 --> 53:33.411
The girls, five and six.

53:33.411 --> 53:35.680
So, we're not very good.

53:35.680 --> 53:40.585
If you could hear them laugh,
you'd understand why I'm here.

53:41.386 --> 53:44.722
Maybe you'd sleep better if you
could see each other easier.

54:20.257 --> 54:22.059
♪ I got some troubles

54:22.059 --> 54:23.828
- ♪ But they won't last...

54:25.496 --> 54:27.465
You like it?

54:27.465 --> 54:29.567
Come to the restaurant,

54:29.567 --> 54:32.837
I can make you all kinds
of breakfast burritos.

54:34.004 --> 54:36.507
They say if you can make
an egg great,

54:36.507 --> 54:37.708
you can do anything.

54:37.708 --> 54:39.977
Eric.

54:39.977 --> 54:44.214
My hands are a little looser.

54:44.214 --> 54:47.284
I just need to get
to the trunk of the car.

54:47.284 --> 54:49.253
- ♪ That liked me some

54:49.253 --> 54:53.691
♪ Never had a friend
or wanted one ♪

54:53.691 --> 54:57.995
♪ So I just lay back and laugh
